docker compose :
- volumes
- networks
- restart policy
- mariadb
- dependencies
- env variables


3 containers, intern communication, no direct access to mariadb, only nginx, tls, persisting volumes

nginx :
- reverse proxy
- tls (open ssl)
- certificat auto signe
- port 442 uniquement

-> installer openssl
-> generer certificat
-> configurer nginx.conf

wordpress :
- php-mysql
- wget / curl
- configurer php fpm
- istallation wordpress
- connexion mariadb

mariadb :
- initialiser bdd
- creer user
- creer base wordpress
- gerer variable env via docker compose



-> terminer service mariadb dans docker compose
-> creer network commun